<title>UK: UK shares start firm, Lloyds gains after results.</title>
<headline>UK shares start firm, Lloyds gains after results.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The UK's FTSE 100 index opened firm on Friday,  pulled higher by Lloyds TSB after in-line results from the banking  group coupled with a better-than-expected dividend.</p>
<p>The FTSE 100 index was up 10.9 points at 4,18.4 by 0735 GMT, with  much of the advance reflecting a sharp 4-1/2 percent rise in Lloyds  shares which added some nine points to the blue chip index.</p>
<p>Lloyds shares were up 29p at 704-1/2, while in the index as a whole  gainers were in a five-to-three majority.</p>
